definition:
παλινγενεσία (Rec. παλιγγ-), -ας, ἡ 
 (πάλιν, γενεσις), 
new birth, renewal, restoration, regeneration; 
   (a) of persons (Plut., Phil., al.), of spiritual regeneration, διὰ λουτροῦ παλινγενεστίας (genitive attr., see Ellic., in l), Tit.3:5; 
   (b) of the world, as in Stoics, Jewish Apocal., al. (see Dalman, Words, 177 ff.), Mat.19:28.†
 (AS)
